      "content": "A red blinking light on your router usually means there is no internet connection, often due to a modem issue or ISP outage. First, try unplugging both your modem and router for about 30 seconds to reset them, then plug the modem back in and wait for its light to turn solid green before reconnecting the router. If the light remains red, check if there are any other users in your area reporting outages, or contact your internet service provider directly for support. Keep in mind that if you tried to unplug a device but it was already unplugged, it might not have been a problem, so ensure the device was actually disconnected before waiting.",
